DOC.brief_title: A Study To Determine Bioequivalence Between The Commercial Femulen Tablets And A Reformulation Of Femulen Tablets In Healthy Female Subjects
DOC.criteria: Body Mass Index ( BMI ) 17.5 30.5 kg/m2 ; total body weight > 45 kg ( 99 lb ) . Healthy female subject age 21 55 year , inclusive . Healthy define clinically relevant abnormality identify detailed medical history , full physical examination , include blood pressure pulse rate measurement , 12lead ECG clinical laboratory test . Evidence history clinically significant hematological , renal , endocrine , pulmonary , gastrointestinal , cardiovascular , hepatic , psychiatric , neurologic , allergic disease ( include drug allergy , exclude untreated , asymptomatic , seasonal allergy time dose ) . Any condition possibly affect drug absorption ( eg , gastrectomy ) .
